Reg. 578/22, s. 2. (2) In this section, “revenue neutral ratio” means the ratio determined under section 5. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2. (3) The tax ratio for the farm property class is 0.25. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2. (6) In the case of a local roads area set out in Table 1, if no tax ratio applied for the property class because the Table indicates that the ratio is not applicable, the tax ratio is 1. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2. (7) In the case of a local roads area set out in Table 1, for a property class other than the farm property class and the managed forests property class, the following rules apply: 1.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is 1, the tax ratio is 1. 2.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is less than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is greater than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the 2022 taxation year. 3.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is less than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is less than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year. 4.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is greater than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is greater than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year. 5.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is greater than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is less than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the 2022 taxation year. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2. (8) Despite subsection (7), the tax ratio for the 2023 taxation year for the Northern Light Lake Local Roads Area for the commercial property class is 1. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

3. (1) This section applies with respect to the determination of the tax ratio for a property class in a local roads area for the purposes of section 21 of the Act for the 2023 taxation year. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(2) In this section,

“revenue neutral ratio” means the ratio determined under section 5. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(3) The tax ratio for the farm property class is 0.25. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(4) The tax ratio for the managed forests property class is 0.25. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(5) In the case of a local roads area that is not set out in Table 1, the tax ratio for a property class other than the farm property class and the managed forests property class is 1. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(6) In the case of a local roads area set out in Table 1, if no tax ratio applied for the property class because the Table indicates that the ratio is not applicable, the tax ratio is 1. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(7) In the case of a local roads area set out in Table 1, for a property class other than the farm property class and the managed forests property class, the following rules apply:

1.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is 1, the tax ratio is 1.

2.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is less than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is greater than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the 2022 taxation year.

3.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is less than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is less than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year.

4.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is greater than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is greater than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year.

5.  If the ratio set out in Table 1 is greater than 1 and the tax ratio for the 2022 taxation year for the property class is less than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the 2023 taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the 2022 taxation year. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(8) Despite subsection (7), the tax ratio for the 2023 taxation year for the Northern Light Lake Local Roads Area for the commercial property class is 1. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

For a property class for which the tax ratio for the previous taxation year is 1, the tax ratio is 1. 2.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is less than 1 and greater than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year. 3.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is less than 1 and less than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year. 4.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is greater than 1 and greater than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year. 5.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is greater than 1 and less than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

4. (1) This section applies with respect to the determination of the tax ratio for a property class in a local roads area for the purposes of section 21 of the Act for a taxation year after 2023. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(2) In this section,

“revenue neutral ratio” means the ratio determined under section 5. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(3) The tax ratio for the farm property class is 0.25. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(4) The tax ratio for the managed forests property class is 0.25. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(5) In the case of a property class, other than the farm property class and the managed forests property class, for which no ratio applied in the previous year, the tax ratio is 1. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(6) In the case of a property class other than the farm property class and the managed forests property class, the following rules apply:

1.  For a property class for which the tax ratio for the previous taxation year is 1, the tax ratio is 1.

2.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is less than 1 and greater than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year.

3.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is less than 1 and less than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year.

4.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is greater than 1 and greater than or equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year.

5.  If the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year is greater than 1 and less than the revenue neutral ratio for the property class for the taxation year, the tax ratio for the property class for the taxation year is equal to the tax ratio for the property class for the previous taxation year. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

content.content:
5. (1) In this section, “specified classes” means the farm property class, the managed forests property class, the residential property class and the multi-residential property class. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2. (2) For the purposes of determining the revenue neutral ratio for a property class in a local roads area under this section, the total assessment for the properties in a property class for the previous year includes all assessments made for the purposes of taxation for the previous year that are made after the return of the roll for the board for the previous year. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2. (3) The revenue neutral ratio for a property class in a local roads area, other than a property class in the specified classes, for a taxation year is determined as follows: 1.  Multiply the tax ratio for the property class for the previous year by the amount of the total assessment of the properties in that property class for the year. 2.  Multiply the tax ratio for the property class for the previous year by the amount of the total assessment of the properties in that property class for the previous year. 3.  Determine the weighted reassessment change for the specified classes by dividing “A” by “B” where, “A”  is the sum of all amounts each of which is an amount determined under paragraph 1 for a property class included in the specified classes, and “B”  is the sum of all amounts each of which is an amount determined under paragraph 2 for a property class included in the specified classes. 4.  Determine the weighted reassessment change for each property class in the local roads area, other than a class in the specified classes, by dividing “C” by “D” where, “C”  is the amount determined under paragraph 1 for the property class, and “D”  is the amount determined under paragraph 2 for the property class. 5.  Determine the adjustment factor for each property class in the local roads area, other than the specified classes, by dividing “E” by “F” where, “E”  is the weighted reassessment change determined for the class under paragraph 4, and “F”  is the weighted reassessment change determined for the specified classes under paragraph 3. 6.  Determine the revenue neutral ratio for a property class in the local roads area for the taxation year by dividing “G” by “H” where, “G”  is the tax ratio for the previous year for the property class, and “H”  is the adjustment factor for the property class determined under paragraph 5. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2. 5. (1) In this section,

“specified classes” means the farm property class, the managed forests property class, the residential property class and the multi-residential property class. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(2) For the purposes of determining the revenue neutral ratio for a property class in a local roads area under this section, the total assessment for the properties in a property class for the previous year includes all assessments made for the purposes of taxation for the previous year that are made after the return of the roll for the board for the previous year. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.

(3) The revenue neutral ratio for a property class in a local roads area, other than a property class in the specified classes, for a taxation year is determined as follows:

1.  Multiply the tax ratio for the property class for the previous year by the amount of the total assessment of the properties in that property class for the year.

2.  Multiply the tax ratio for the property class for the previous year by the amount of the total assessment of the properties in that property class for the previous year.

3.  Determine the weighted reassessment change for the specified classes by dividing “A” by “B” where,

“A”  is the sum of all amounts each of which is an amount determined under paragraph 1 for a property class included in the specified classes, and

“B”  is the sum of all amounts each of which is an amount determined under paragraph 2 for a property class included in the specified classes.

4.  Determine the weighted reassessment change for each property class in the local roads area, other than a class in the specified classes, by dividing “C” by “D” where,

“C”  is the amount determined under paragraph 1 for the property class, and

“D”  is the amount determined under paragraph 2 for the property class.

5.  Determine the adjustment factor for each property class in the local roads area, other than the specified classes, by dividing “E” by “F” where,

“E”  is the weighted reassessment change determined for the class under paragraph 4, and

“F”  is the weighted reassessment change determined for the specified classes under paragraph 3.

6.  Determine the revenue neutral ratio for a property class in the local roads area for the taxation year by dividing “G” by “H” where,

“G”  is the tax ratio for the previous year for the property class, and

“H”  is the adjustment factor for the property class determined under paragraph 5. O. Reg. 578/22, s. 2.
